Problem Statement 1

About half (47.4%) of Brazil’s economic activity is concentrated in the Southeastern states of São Paulo, Rio de Janeiro, and Minas Gerais. Important domestic industries include agriculture, mining, services and manufacturing. According to commodity.com, “Any adverse commodity price developments have a direct impact on the Brazilian economy and any slowdown in China, which accounts for anywhere from 18% to 29% of Brazil’s total exports, will put further pressure on the economic performance of the country.” Such an export concentration, whether in export destination or the export's location of production, can have a large effect on the economy in case of supply chain disruptions, geopolitical tension, pandemics and more.
